om Argentina to Zimbabwe, including notable examples from Brazil, India, Nigeria, Russia, and the United States-touching on the 2016 election. This eye-opening study offers a sobering overview of corrupted professional politics, while providing fertile intellectual ground for the development of new solutions for protecting democracy from authoritarian subversion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aElectionsxCorrupt practiceszDeveloping countries. 0aElectionsxCorrupt practices. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aKlaas, Brian, eauthor.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235210423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235210.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles